AUGUST 2010
Welcome Onboard
ELEVATING
AIRLINE FOOD TO A
HIGHER STANDARD
We are taking our Northern Bites food-for-purchase options to a whole new level as we offer a hot, fresh
meal for purchase on almost every flight longer than 2½ hours. Now you'll have the option of a delicious
fresh meal or Picnic Pack on twice as many flights.
The secret ingredient behind all our First Class menus and Northern Bites enhancements is our
Executive Chef Clifton Lyles. Chef Cliff, as we call him, shares our passion for great airline food. He used
to run his own catering company, but now he relishes the challenge of delivering delicious meals served
at more than 30,000 feet.
"Alaska Airlines takes their responsibilities to their customers seriously," says Chef Cliff. "So the fact that I
get to help run the 450 restaurants they fly every day is a great honor."
Check out our new options on the following pages. Better yet, try one. Let us know what you think — drop
Chef Cliff a note at Chef. Cliff@alaskaair.com. Thanks for flying with us today.
